@article{Brown2016,
abstract = {{\textless}i{\textgreater}Context. {\textless}i/{\textgreater}At about 1000 days after the launch of {\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia {\textless}i/{\textgreater}we present the first {\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia {\textless}i/{\textgreater}data release, {\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia{\textless}i/{\textgreater} DR1, consisting of astrometry and photometry for over 1 billion sources brighter than magnitude 20.7.{\textless}i{\textgreater}Aims. {\textless}i/{\textgreater}A summary of {\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia{\textless}i/{\textgreater} DR1 is presented along with illustrations of the scientific quality of the data, followed by a discussion of the limitations due to the preliminary nature of this release.{\textless}i{\textgreater}Methods. {\textless}i/{\textgreater}The raw data collected by {\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia {\textless}i/{\textgreater}during the first 14 months of the mission have been processed by the {\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia {\textless}i/{\textgreater}Data Processing and Analysis Consortium (DPAC) and turned into an astrometric and photometric catalogue.{\textless}i{\textgreater}Results. {\textless}i/{\textgreater}{\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia{\textless}i/{\textgreater} DR1 consists of three components: a primary astrometric data set which contains the positions, parallaxes, and mean proper motions for about 2 million of the brightest stars in common with the Hipparcos and {\textless}i{\textgreater}Tycho{\textless}i/{\textgreater}-2 catalogues – a realisation of the {\textless}i{\textgreater}Tycho{\textless}i/{\textgreater}-{\textless}i{\textgreater}Gaia {\textless}i/{\textgreater}Astrometric Solution (TGAS) – and a secondary astrometric data set containing the positions for an additional 1.1 billion sources. The second component is the photometric data set, consisting of mean {\textless}i{\textgreater}G{\textless}i/{\textgreater}-band magnitudes for all sources. The {\textless}i{\textgreater}G{\textless}i/{\textgreater}-band light cu